liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: So Carlton kick the first five, and Brisbane kick the next three. We've got a game at the Gabba, folks!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 15': Daniher makes no mistake! Lions have three in a row!

children.content: So Carlton kick the first five, and Brisbane kick the next three.
We've got a game at the Gabba, folks!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Chris Fagan got that group in and no doubt delivered some very stern words. Will a Brisbane response come?
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 20': The second quarter is underway

children.content: Chris Fagan got that group in and no doubt delivered some very stern words.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well. Given the occasion, that's the best quarter of Carlton footy in how long? 28 years? The relentless pressure from the Blues set up that five-goal-to-one opening quarter, but it was their poise and impenetrable defensive structure that saw them capitalise on it. Not sure Michael Voss could have asked for more. Sam Walsh playing well, Harry McKay playing really well. Small forwards swarming, Jacob Weitering and Mitch McGovern locking things down at the back. If not for Harris Andrews, things could be looking even worse for Brisbane. But they're a long way from out of this. Four goals is nothing for a team with their scoring power. A brilliant start for the Blues, but this is miles from over.
